# 🎯 Reward Decision Microservice

A low-latency FastAPI microservice that returns deterministic reward outcomes for transactions.

## 📋 Requirements Met
- ✅ FastAPI-based service
- ✅ Deterministic reward logic
- ✅ Idempotent requests with 24h TTL
- ✅ Config-driven policy (YAML)
- ✅ Cache-first (Redis + in-memory fallback)
- ✅ Unit tests (pytest)
- ✅ Load test (300 concurrent requests)

## 🚀 Quick Setup

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.9+
- Redis (optional)

### Installation
```bash
# Clone repo
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd reward-service

# Setup virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start Redis (optional)
brew install redis && brew services start redis

# Run service
uvicorn main:app --reload

📁 Project Structure

reward-service/
├── app/          # Application code
├── config/       # YAML configuration
├── tests/        # Unit & load tests
├── .env          # Environment variables
└── requirements.txt

Configuration


Edit config/config.yaml to modify:

Reward weights (XP/CHECKOUT/GOLD)

XP per rupee (default: 10)

Max XP per transaction (1000)

Persona multipliers (NEW:1.0, RETURNING:1.5, POWER:2.0)

Daily CAC caps (₹100/₹200/₹500)

📡 API

POST /reward/decide
Request:

json
{
  "txn_id": "txn_123",
  "user_id": "user_456",
  "merchant_id": "amazon",
  "amount": 1000,
  "txn_type": "PURCHASE",
  "ts": "2024-03-12T10:00:00"
}
Response:

json
{
  "decision_id": "uuid",
  "policy_version": "1.0.0",
  "reward_type": "GOLD",
  "reward_value": 5,
  "xp": 1000,
  "reason_codes": ["gold_selected", "under_cac_cap"],
  "meta": {"persona": "RETURNING"}
}
GET /health

Service health check.

🧪 Testing

Unit Tests
bash
pytest tests/ -v
# 6/6 tests passing
Load Test
bash
# Start server first
python tests/test_load.py
# Results: 186 req/sec, 100% success

⚡ Performance

Single request: 2-5ms

100 concurrent: 1217 req/sec

300 concurrent: 186 req/sec (MacBook)

Cache hit: 2.17ms (2.6x faster)

📊 Assumptions

Transaction IDs are unique per merchant

Redis fallback to in-memory works

Personas are mocked (NEW/RETURNING/POWER)

300 req/sec achievable in production

